			<div class="content" id="post-content-3784037">
									

<blockquote>
<p>We started outsourcing.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>There's several issues I have with this piece; this line's just one of them. What you're trying to do is <em>really</em> hard, so I can't fault you for trying (if anything, I like the fact that you just <em>went</em> for it like this; that's one reason I'm not down-voting).</p>
<p>On the other hand, a Chicago gang-member using a term like &quot;outsourcing&quot;? In <em>1931</em>? This is what makes a document like this so challenging: You need to make it both historically sensible (it needs to look like something a 1931 anomalous criminal organization would produce) while also being compelling on its own.</p>
<p>This is a huge challenge, and something I would expect requires a lot of research to get &quot;right&quot;. As an example of something I think does this just right: <a href="/a-history-of-reaction">A History of Reaction</a>, by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2038009&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1524967979" alt="TyGently" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2038009)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tygently" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2038009); return false;">TyGently</a></span>.</p>

							</div>

								
